'''Embryokines''' ([[Greek language|Greek]]: ''embryuon'' "embryo" + ''kinōs'' "movement") are regulatory molecules produced by the reproductive tract that modulate [[embryonic development]].<ref>{{cite journal |vauthors=Hansen PJ, Dobbs KD, Denicol AC |title=Programming of the preimplantation embryo by the embryokine colony stimulating factor 2 |journal=Animal Reproduction Science |volume=149 |issue=1-2 |pages=59–66 |date=September 2014 |pmid=24954585 |doi=10.1016/j.anireprosci.2014.05.017}}</ref>
Among the molecules that function as embryokines are [[insulin-like growth factor-1]],<ref>{{cite journal |vauthors=Block J, Hansen PJ, Loureiro B, Bonilla L |title=Improving post-transfer survival of bovine embryos produced in vitro: actions of insulin-like growth factor-1, colony stimulating factor-2 and hyaluronan. |journal=Theriogeniology |volume=76 |issue=9 |pages=1602–1609 |date=December 2011 |pmid=21890189 |doi=10.1016/j.theriogenology.2011.07.025}}</ref> [[cytokines]] (e.g., [[colony stimulating factor 2]]),<ref>{{cite journal |vauthors=Hansen PJ, Dobbs KD, Denicol AC |title=Programming of the preimplantation embryo by the embryokine colony stimulating factor 2 |journal=Animal Reproduction Science |volume=149 |issue=1-2 |pages=59–66 |date=September 2014 |pmid=24954585 |doi=10.1016/j.anireprosci.2014.05.017}}</ref> WNT regulatory proteins (i.e., [[DKK1]]<ref>{{cite journal |vauthors=Denicol AC, Block J, Kelley KG, Dobbs KB, Mortensen CJ, Ortega MS, Hansen PJ |title=The WNT signaling antagonist Dickkopf-1 directs lineage commitment and promotes survival of the preimplantation embryo. |journal=FASEB Journal |volume=28 |issue=9 |pages=3975–3986 |date=September 2014 |pmid=24858280 |doi=10.1096/fj.14-253112}}</ref> and members of the [[transforming growth factor]] family (e.g., [[activin]]).<ref>{{cite journal |vauthors= Yoshioka K, Suzuki C, Iwamura S |title=Effects of activin A and follistatin on developmental kinetics of bovine embryos: cinematographic analysis in a chemically defined medium. |journal=Journal of Reproduction and Fertility |volume=118 |issue=1 |pages=119–125 |date=January 2000 |pmid=10793633 |doi=10.1530/jrf.0.1180119}}</ref>
