{{one source|date=April 2011}} '''Genetypes''' is a taxonomic concept proposed in 2010 to describe any [[genetic sequence|genetic sequences]] from [[type (biology)|type specimens]].<ref name=Chakrabarty2010>{{cite journal|last=Chakrabarty|first=Prosanta|title=Genetypes: a concept to help integrate molecular systematics and traditional taxonomy|journal=Zootaxa|year=2010|volume=2632|pages=67–68|url=http://www.mapress.com/zootaxa/2010/f/zt02632p068.pdf}}</ref><ref name=Harrisonetal2011>{{cite journal|last=Harrison|first=I. J.|author2=Chakrabarty, P. |author3=Freyhof, J. |author4= Craig, J. F. |title=Correct nomenclature and recommendations for preserving and cataloguing voucher material and genetic sequences|journal=Journal of Fish Biology|date=May 2011|volume=78|issue=5|pages=1283–1290|doi=10.1111/j.1095-8649.2011.02979.x|url=http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1111/j.1095-8649.2011.02979.x/full}}</ref> This nomenclature integrates [[molecular systematics]] and terms used in [[Taxonomy (biology)|biological taxonomy]]. This nomenclature is designed to label, or flag, genetic sequences that were sampled from type specimens. The nomenclature of genetypes proposes that genetic sequences from a [[holotype]] should be referred to as a “hologenetype” (from: '''holo'''type and '''genetype'''), sequences from a topotype will be a “topogenetype,” and so forth. In addition, the genetic marker(s) used should also be incorporated into the nomenclature (e.g., paragenetype ND2).
The genetypes nomenclatural system could be used to flag “gold standard” sequences that due to their direct link to type specimens will be more credible than standard sequences whose species identification may be problematic. Misidentifications plague many sequences on [[GenBank]]{{cn|date=December 2013}} and having some sequences that are linked to type specimens will help locate and manage misidentifications and to create positively identified "gold standard" sequences available for comparison. It is suggested that this nomenclature be used in publications and databases that display or discuss sequences from type specimens.<ref>{{cite web|title=JFB Instruction to Authors |url=http://www.wiley.com/bw/submit.asp?ref=0022-1112 |publisher=Journal of Fish Biology }}{{dead link|date=January 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><ref name=Harrisonetal2011/>
Examples of genetypes include: *''[[Leptoderma]] macrophthalmum'' hologenetype mitogenome - [https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nuccore/AP011500 AP011500] <ref>{{cite journal|first=Ingvar|last= Byrkjedal |author2=Jan Yde Poulsen |author3=John Galbraith|title=''Leptoderma macrophthalmum'' n.sp., a new species of smooth-head (Otocephala: Alepocephalidae) from the Mid Atlantic Ridge|journal=Zootaxa|year= 2011|volume=2876|pages= 49–56|url=http://www.mapress.com/zootaxa/2011/f/z02876p056f.pdf}}</ref> *''[[Milyeringa]] brooksi'' paragenetype COI - [https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nuccore/HM590595 HM590595]<ref name=CHAKRABARTY2010b>{{cite journal|last=Chakrabarty|first=Prosanta|title=Status and phylogeny of Milyeringidae (Teleostei: Gobiiformes), with the description of a new blind cave-fish from Australia, ''Milyeringa brooksi'', n. sp.|journal=Zootaxa|volume=2557|pages=19–28|year=2010|url=http://www.mapress.com/zootaxa/2010/f/z02557p028f.pdf}}</ref> *''Milyeringa brooksi'' paragenetype NDI - [https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nuccore/HM590607 HM590607]<ref name=CHAKRABARTY2010b/>
The genetypes concept was superseded by the [[GenSeq]] concept, proposed in 2013 due to some confusion among researchers that genetypes were equivalent to [[name-bearing type]]s.<ref name=Chakrabarty2013>{{cite journal|last=Chakrabarty|first=Prosanta|author2=Warren, Melanie |author3=Page, Lawrence |author4= Baldwin, Carole |title=GenSeq: An updated nomenclature and ranking for genetic sequences from type and non-type sources|journal=ZooKeys|year=2013|volume=346|pages=29–41|doi=10.3897/zookeys.346.5753|pmid=24223486 |pmc=3821064}}</ref>{{clarification needed|reason=What does "genetypes were equivalent to name-bearing types" mean?|date=February 2014}}
