===Abolitionism===

In these countries, there is no specific law prohibiting the exchange of sex for money, but in general most forms of [[Procuring (prostitution)|procuring]] (pimping) are illegal. These countries also generally have laws against soliciting in a public place (e.g., a street) or advertising prostitution, making it difficult to engage in prostitution without breaking any law. In countries like [[India]], though prostitution is legal, it is illegal when committed in a [[hotel]].<ref name="indiankanoon.org">{{cite web|url=http://indiankanoon.org/doc/139656816/ |title=Section 7 in The Immoral Traffic (Prevention) Act, 1956 |publisher=Indiankanoon.org |date= |accessdate=2015-09-07}}</ref>

