===Neo-abolitionism===
In these countries, although prostitutes themselves commit no crime, clients and any third party involvement is criminalised.<ref name="canada" /> Also called the "Swedish model" or "Nordic model".<ref name="catwa" /><ref name="lse" />

* Americas: [[Belize]];<ref>{{cite web|last1=Flowers|first1=Benjamin|title=Regional prostitution laws challenged but sex work already legal in Belize|url=http://www.reporter.bz/front-page/regional-prostitution-laws-challenged-but-sex-work-already-legal-in-belize/|website=The Reporter Newspaper|accessdate=31 December 2017|date=22 April 2016}}</ref> [[Canada]];<ref name="spl" /> [[Martinique]];<ref name="boulai">{{cite web|last1=Boulai|first1=Melinda|title=Prostitution : une vie de misère et des rêves d&#039;ailleurs - Toute l&#039;actualité de la Martinique sur Internet - FranceAntilles.fr|url=http://www.martinique.franceantilles.fr/actualite/une/prostitution-une-vie-de-misere-et-des-reves-d-ailleurs-274273.php|website=France-Antilles Martinique|accessdate=28 December 2017|language=fr-FR|date=4 October 2014}}</ref>
